oc:kn_0e0d6965 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before generating any charts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify ALL three prerequisite tasks (1: Company Research, 2: Financial Model, 3: Valuation Analysis) are complete before starting. Check: company history/milestones, management team, product portfolio, customer segmentation, competitive landscape, TAM, revenue breakdowns, margin trends, scenario data, DCF sensitivity, comps data, valuation ranges, and external stock price data." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Charts require data from all three prior tasks plus external sources. Starting without complete data results in incomplete or placeholder charts that undermine report quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_0ec95962 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before executing chart generation scripts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Python libraries required: matplotlib, seaborn, pandas, numpy, plotly. Install via: pip install matplotlib seaborn pandas numpy plotly" ;
    oc:hasRationale "These libraries provide the charting, data manipulation, and styling capabilities needed for professional financial visualizations." .

oc:kn_3c735f4f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any chart" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All charts must use consistent professional formatting: 300 DPI resolution, 10x6 inch figure size, white background, seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid style, clear figure numbering (sequential), source citations at bottom, no fonts smaller than 9pt, remove top/right spines." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent styling ensures the chart package looks professional when embedded in the final DOCX report and meets print quality standards." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_596e5496 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining which charts to create" ;
    oc:directiveContent "4 charts are MANDATORY and non-negotiable: chart_03 (Revenue by Product stacked area), chart_04 (Revenue by Geography stacked bar), chart_28 (DCF Sensitivity heatmap), chart_32 (Valuation Football Field horizontal bar). All 4 must be present for Task 5 to succeed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These 4 charts are the critical visualizations for the financial analysis and valuation sections that define the report's analytical credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_5cef77d4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When encountering chart rendering problems" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Common issues and fixes: Low resolution → ensure dpi=300 in savefig(); Text cutoff → use bbox_inches='tight'; Poor colors → use Tableau10 palette or custom corporate colors; Overlapping labels → rotate 45° or reduce font; Excess whitespace → call tight_layout() before saving." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the most frequent matplotlib issues that degrade chart quality and can be fixed with simple parameter adjustments." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_7d00e820 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing visualization types for each data set" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Chart type selection: Line charts for time series trends, Stacked Area for revenue composition over time, Stacked Bar for geographic/quarterly breakdowns, Heatmap for sensitivity matrices, Horizontal Bar for valuation ranges, Waterfall for build-up analysis, Scatter/Bubble for growth vs. valuation comparisons, 2x2 Matrix for competitive positioning." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Correct chart type selection ensures data is communicated clearly and matches institutional research conventions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7e354c40 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating revenue composition charts" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# Stacked area chart (Revenue by Product)
ax.stackplot(years, *product_arrays, labels=product_names, colors=colors, alpha=0.8)
ax.axvline(x=hist_cutoff_year, color='gray', linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.5)
ax.text(hist_cutoff_year+0.2, ax.get_ylim()[1]*0.95, 'Projected →', fontsize=9, color='gray')""" .

oc:kn_92b04a83 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing the full chart generation workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Verify all prerequisites (Tasks 1-3 complete + external data). 2. Set up Python environment (install libs, configure global style: 300 DPI, 10x6 figures, seaborn style). 3. Extract data from model/valuation into Python variables. 4. Create 4 mandatory charts (chart_03, 04, 28, 32). 5. Create remaining 21 required charts. 6. Optionally create 1-10 additional charts for visual density. 7. Generate chart_index.txt. 8. Run quality verification. 9. Package into zip file." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_951f8eed a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When naming and formatting charts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Number charts by their report position, not creation order. Use format chart_[NUMBER]_[DESCRIPTION].png. Separate historical from projected data with a vertical dashed line and 'Projected →' label." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Report-position numbering ensures charts map correctly to Task 5 embedding locations. Historical/projected separation maintains analytical integrity." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_9cb9286a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After all charts are generated" ;
    oc:directiveContent "After generation, verify: (1) all 4 mandatory charts exist, (2) total chart count is 25-35, (3) each file is >50KB (confirms 300 DPI), (4) chart_index.txt is created with all entries. Package into [Company]_Charts_[Date].zip." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Quality verification prevents low-resolution or missing charts from reaching the final report assembly stage." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a080aa3a a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating DCF sensitivity analysis visualization" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# DCF Sensitivity Heatmap
df = pd.DataFrame(sensitivity_matrix, index=[f'{w}%' for w in wacc_values], columns=[f'{g}%' for g in terminal_growth])
sns.heatmap(df, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='RdYlGn', cbar_kws={'label': 'Price per Share ($)'}, linewidths=0.5, ax=ax)""" .

oc:kn_a3b3ccb4 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any financial chart" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')
sns.set_palette('husl')

DPI = 300
FIGURE_WIDTH = 10
FIGURE_HEIGHT = 6

# Template for each chart:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(FIGURE_WIDTH, FIGURE_HEIGHT))
# ... plot data ...
ax.set_title('Figure N - Title', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
fig.text(0.12, 0.02, 'Source: [Firm] estimates', fontsize=9, style='italic', color='gray')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('chart_NN_name.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='white')
plt.close()""" .

oc:kn_aa2883d7 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When naming and packaging output files" ;
    oc:directiveContent """chart_[NUMBER]_[DESCRIPTION].png — 300 DPI, PNG format, white background
Chart Index: chart_index.txt listing all charts with descriptions and mandatory/optional status
Package: [Company]_Charts_[Date].zip containing all charts + index""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Company",
        "DESCRIPTION",
        "Date",
        "NUMBER" .

oc:kn_fa838f1d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When prerequisite data is missing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create placeholder charts or skip charts due to missing prerequisite data. If Tasks 1, 2, or 3 are incomplete, stop immediately and inform the user which tasks need completion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Placeholder charts destroy report credibility and mislead readers. Missing data must be resolved at the source." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

